{"ts":"2026-06-27T18:29:23.842Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"imjimixb","input":{"summary":"Successfully connected both the Admin Documents and Billing pages to their respective backend CRUD APIs (/api/v1/documents and /api/v1/invoices).\n\n### Key Accomplishments:\n1. **Admin Documents Registry (/admin/documents)**:\n   - Wired up dynamic document metadata listing from the backend `GET /api/v1/documents` endpoint.\n   - Connected target project listings to `GET /api/v1/projects` so sandbox mappings dynamically fetch from the active enclaves.\n   - Implemented real creation via `POST /api/v1/documents`, mapping client names to their active backend IDs (`client-001` through `client-004`).\n   - Integrated project re-assignment and compliance checklist toggle updates via `PATCH /api/v1/documents/[id]`.\n   - Enabled secure document metadata deprovisioning via `DELETE /api/v1/documents/[id]`.\n   - Introduced dynamic `loading` and `error` states with premium loaders and \"Retry Handshake\" banners.\n\n2. **Admin Billing Operations (/admin/billing)**:\n   - Configured dynamic invoice listing from the backend `GET /api/v1/invoices` endpoint.\n   - Tied the premium step-by-step signing flow to actually perform a `POST /api/v1/invoices` on successful ECC-256 seal completion, establishing dynamic invoices in memory.\n   - Wired up the Settle Payment button to perform a `PATCH /api/v1/invoices/[id]` with status set to `paid`.\n   - Designed and built a premium \"Archive Ledger Block\" trash action button next to the close drawer button, fully wired to the backend `DELETE /api/v1/invoices/[id]` endpoint.\n   - Integrated dynamic `loading` and `error` states with a skeleton calculator loader and standard retry handlers.\n\n3. **Validation and Build Check**:\n   - Verified TypeScript compilation and Next.js routing structures by running `npx tsc --noEmit`, which successfully completed with no type or compilation errors.\n   - Maintained all Phase 4 premium Figma styles, neon theme accents, Apple-like micro-interactions, responsive mobile configurations, and guardrail constraints.","verified":true}}}
